The paper deals with resource allocation and beamforming in interference networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the joint performance of multiple systems, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of beamforming vectors and covariance matrices is related to multimedia systems (cs.MM), and the discussion of Pareto optimality is related to game theory (cs.GT).
